      "message": "the current CreateParameters enum is shared across IBM dump creation parameters, so the interface does not strongly express which parameters apply to each dump type.\nFor this patch, I was trying to follow the existing CreateDump  documentation, where AdditionalData keys are expected to use the *.Dump.Create.CreateParameters.* enum-string format. \n\nMoving SBE-specific parameters under a separate SBEDumpParameters enum would be a larger interface redesign and may require updates to the base dump-create documentation and existing consumers.\nI have improved the clarity in this patch by documenting the applicability explicitly to clear any ambiguity, for example:\n\nSBEDumpTriggerType: valid only when DumpType is SBE\nDumpFilesPath: path to the collected dump files, currently used by SBE dump creation\nIf we want to reorganize dump parameters by category, I think that should be handled as a separate cleanup/design change so we can update the common interface documentaion and existing callers consistently.",
